WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:01.320
<v Stephane>Hey, so we are going to learn</v>

2
00:00:01.320 --> 00:00:02.153
about CodeCommit,

3
00:00:02.153 --> 00:00:05.190
but on July 25th, 2024,

4
00:00:05.190 --> 00:00:07.470
AWS decided to discontinue this service.

5
00:00:07.470 --> 00:00:09.630
So new customers cannot use the service,

6
00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:11.220
and AWS is recommending you

7
00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:13.020
to migrate to another Git solution

8
00:00:13.020 --> 00:00:15.960
such as GitHub, GitLab, or a 3rd party git.

9
00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:18.120
So you don't know what it is yet, but we'll see this soon.

10
00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:21.090
But for this course, CodeCommit might still appear

11
00:00:21.090 --> 00:00:22.470
at the exam for now.

12
00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:25.590
And so therefore, I keep the CodeCommit lectures.

13
00:00:25.590 --> 00:00:28.200
And every time I mention CodeCommit in the course,

14
00:00:28.200 --> 00:00:30.000
and it could be in many different places,

15
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.010
assume that there's a GitHub integration

16
00:00:32.010 --> 00:00:33.240
and don't get freaked out

17
00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:36.360
because well, CodeCommit is just a GitHub replacement,

18
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:38.580
and that's all you need to know, as you will see very soon.

19
00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:40.410
So that's it. You should be good for the course.

20
00:00:40.410 --> 00:00:42.570
Don't worry if you see CodeCommit here and there,

21
00:00:42.570 --> 00:00:43.830
it really doesn't matter.

22
00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:47.370
But now you know everything about this unfortunate event.

23
00:00:47.370 --> 00:00:48.240
All right, that's it.

24
00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:49.350
I hope you liked it

25
00:00:49.350 --> 00:00:51.300
and I will see you in the next lecture.

